s there in time to take the mob.<P>The problem with Ragefire is strictly in the hands of VI in my opinion.  They created this situation and it is "working as intended".  <P>Poor planning, but what is there to do?<P>If there was a list on my server, I would honor it.  I just question whether other folks on my server would.<P>Tarf</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">naxy</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">If Bristlebane had a list then I would honor it too. I believe that it is worth a try, even though a small minority will not honor it.<P>Start a list of Clerics on Bristlebane who does honor it. But wouldn't the Bristlebane boards be the placed to keep it?<P>------------------<BR>Naxy Dent, Cleric of Oasis Covenant on Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Corynthia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Its a nice idea, I´m ready to support this.<BR>and I think many others would to.<BR>I know several clerics who have given up on gettin the epic because all this bickering and BS surrounding the ragefire.<P>------------------<BR>Corynthia<BR>55th Level Dwarven Vicar<BR>United Kingdom<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Electro</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Even though such a list is the only way I could ever reasonably hope to get the Epic I don't see any way that it could ever be done on Bristlebane. There are simply way way too many clerics who would be on such a list, meaning the benefit of circumventing it for the people who "don't want to wait" is so high that they will circumvent it.<P>Electro<BR>Templar of Karana<BR>Bristlebane</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Cayleu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I wish you luck, but Tarf is correct. This is going to